Finance
Responsibilities
Job DescriptionResponsible for all aspects in finance, accounting and taxation areas of the Company which includes ensuring all the reporting compliances to Corporate Office and other requirementsIn charges in the annual budget preparation which includes the review and control the variancesEstablish a written accounting policies and procedures for better control and improve efficiencyPlan, monitor and control the inventory movements in order to avoid any potential loss from inventory and improve the stock turnoverDesign the effective procedure for the front-end and warehouse teams for better control and reporting process which includes daily sales procedures, credit card procedures as well as receiving of inventoryManage the company’s cash flowWork closely with other departments in improving the performance of organizationProvide recommendations to the management to achieve Company’s goals and objectivesAssist the Country Director in strategic planning, managing core and significant issues of the CompanyLiaise directly with third parties such as principals, auditor, contractors, insurance agent, landlords and bankers, etc  QualificationMale, age between 30 - 35 years oldCandidate must possess at least a Bachelor’s Degree, majoring of Economy, AccountancyAt least 5 years of working experience in the related field is required for this position (3 years in managerial level)Experience in retail industry would be advantageous2 years experience in a Big Four Public Accounting FirmsHaving knowledge of Accounting, Finance, Audit & Taxation, Assets management, Internal control procedures, Cash flow management, Banking and logisticFluent in written and spoken EnglishGood interpersonal skills, leadership skills, analytical skillsAble to work under pressure Your CV should be completed with photo, current and expected salary. Send your application (quote the code in the email subject) to :HRD – PT Gagan IndonesiaEmail :  jessica.andia@gagan.co.id(attachment size max 800 kb)
